        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 4:05PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers and isolated
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Augusta to just south
of Great Falls to near Hobson. Movement was north at 30 mph. Expect
a period of rain and gusty winds up to 45 mph as this area of
precipitation arrives with isolated stronger thunderstorm cells
producing lightning and brief heavier rain. This area of
precipitation will reach as far north as Choteau to Highwood by 500
PM.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Choteau, Stanford, Fairfield, Belt, Dutton, Fort  Shaw,
Highwood, Black Eagle, Geyser, Fort Shaw, Power, Carter, Floweree,
Pishkun Reservoir, Windham, Stockett, Utica, First Peoples Buffalo
Jump State Park, and Shonkin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
